etymology.description: 目(目) (mù, "eye") + 袁(袁) as phonetic = to see clearly -> vision-related
etymology.interpretation: The character 睘(qióng, "to see clearly") combines the semantic element 目(目) (mù, "eye"), indicating vision, with the phonetic 袁(袁), which helps convey the pronunciation, thus relating to the concept of clear vision.
